data.description: Motivated Seller! Need some closing cost assistance OR a paint credit OR maybe prepaid HOA for a year?? YOU GOT IT! This spacious floor plan is one of the best in the neighborhood with 20ft high ceilings in the family room and lots of natural light. Great home with lots of space for entertaining. The living room/dining room combination flows to the kitchen with lots of cabinets for storage, a pantry and plenty of countertop space.  The screened in porch off the kitchen backs to a private wooded area.The upstairs offers 3 generous bedrooms. The primary has a walk-in closet and garden tub/shower combo.  The laundry room is upstairs plus another full bath.  This home has a one-car garage and off-street parking. HVAC is 2022. Carpets just cleaned. Refrigerator conveys.No weekends of yard work here! PAINT QUOTE IN HAND. HOA coverage makes this home practically maintenance  free...water/sewer, lawn care, landscaping (inside any fence is an owner's responsibility), irrigation system, neighborhood pools, termite bond, annual pressure washing,  and exterior insurance . 10 minutes to Historic Downtown Summerville.  Close to shopping and restaurants. All within 30 minutes: Boeing, Volvo, Airport, Bosch, Hospitals, Jt Base CHS and downtown Charleston.
